ound economic and social transformation. All of the men Rico discusses-from the well known, including Theodore Roosevelt and Buffalo Bill Cody, to the comparatively obscure, such as English cattle rancher Moreton Frewen-envisioned the American West as a global space into which redemptive narratives of heroic upper-class masculinity could be written.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aBritishzWest (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezWest (U.S.) 0aMasculinityzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aMasculinityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aUpper classzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aUpper classzWest (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300196252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300196252.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles